# SubTrak Core Rules

## Architecture
- Next.js App Router with TypeScript strict mode
- shadcn/ui before custom UI components
- Modular, reusable components; small focused files
- Server-safe patterns: secrets only in server code (API routes, server components)

## File Ownership
Before any change, identify: which file owns the logic, whether it belongs in UI / business logic / API / database, and whether an existing util already solves it.

## Separation of Concerns
- UI components: no heavy business logic
- API routes: no duplicated parsing; use shared Zod schemas from `lib/validations/`
- Database logic: isolated in Prisma queries via `lib/prisma.ts`
- AI parsing: `lib/ai.ts`
- Auth helpers: `lib/auth.ts`

## No Duplication
If similar logic appears twice, refactor into shared utilities/hooks/components.

## Safe & Explicit Code
- Validate all input with Zod
- Handle loading, error, and empty states in every screen
- Never use `any` unless unavoidable; prefer strong types
- No magic strings; use enums and constants

## Correction Memory Format
For every correction:
```
- Mistake:
- Root cause:
- Fix:
- Prevention rule:
```

When a mistake repeats, refactor the system rather than patching. If the user says a previous approach was wrong, pivot immediately.

## Delivery
After each substantial change, note: changed files, what changed, why, and any follow-up risks.
